_exec_summary.SummaryText:
afety



The Facility resolves all findings from HAZOP studies, some of which result in modifications to the process.  The resolutions and resulting changes are tracked internally to ensure completion.  Findings from the most recent PHA have not yet been formally approved for implementation.  Other changes that have been completed or are being considered for implementation within the MAN unit include:

-    Drainage trenching within the process unit to remove hazardous chemicals spills from the immediate process area;

-    Construction of security fencing around the butane sphere;

-    Updates to MOC program to facilitate transition to an electronic system.

Finally, within the coming months, FHR will be revising the Facility (including the MAN unit) MOC process so that MOC reviews are managed and tracked through an electronic system.  The MOC procedures will be updated to incorporate the revised MOC methodologies.
